WEBVTT

00:15.800 --> 00:16.420
III.

00:18.720 --> 00:23.860
Now in the fifteenth year of the reign of Tiberius Caesar, Pontius Pilate being governor

00:23.860 --> 00:30.000
of Judea, and Herod being tetrarch of Galilee, and his brother Philip tetrarch of Ituraea,

00:30.180 --> 00:36.300
and of the region of Trachonitis, and Lysanius the tetrarch of Abilene, Anas and Caiaphas

00:36.300 --> 00:41.860
being the high priests, the word of God came unto John the son of Zacharias in the wilderness.

00:42.520 --> 00:47.600
And he came into all the country about Jordan preaching the baptism of repentance for the

00:47.600 --> 00:48.720
remission of sins.

00:49.570 --> 00:52.020
As it is written in the book of the words of

00:52.020 --> 00:57.160
Isaias the prophet, saying, The voice of one crying in the wilderness,

00:57.840 --> 01:02.380
Prepare ye the way of the Lord, make his paths straight.

01:03.380 --> 01:08.000
Every valley shall be filled, and every mountain and hill shall be brought low,

01:08.440 --> 01:12.980
And the crooked shall be made straight, and the rough ways shall be made smooth,

01:13.200 --> 01:15.920
And all flesh shall see the salvation of God.

01:16.640 --> 01:20.440
Then said he to the multitude that came forth to be baptized of him,

01:21.160 --> 01:26.000
O generation of vipers, who hath warned you to flee from the wrath to come?

01:26.780 --> 01:32.500
Bring forth therefore fruits worthy of repentance, and begin not to say within yourselves,

01:33.160 --> 01:39.060
We have Abraham to our father, for I say unto you that God is able of these stones

01:39.060 --> 01:41.020
To raise up children unto Abraham.

01:41.860 --> 01:45.480
And now also the axe is laid unto the root of the trees,

01:46.120 --> 01:50.640
Every tree therefore which bringeth not forth good fruit is hewn down,

01:51.060 --> 01:52.520
And cast into the fire.

01:53.260 --> 01:56.840
And the people asked him, saying, What shall we do then?

01:57.260 --> 02:02.740
He answereth and saith unto them, He that hath two coats, let him impart to him

02:02.740 --> 02:06.580
That hath none, and he that hath meat, let him do likewise.

02:07.350 --> 02:11.460
Then came also publicans to be baptized, and said unto him,

02:11.860 --> 02:14.200
Master, what shall we do?

02:14.600 --> 02:19.560
And he said unto them, Exact no more than that which has appointed you.

02:20.520 --> 02:25.000
And the soldiers likewise demanded of him, saying, And what shall we do?

02:25.220 --> 02:30.780
And he said unto them, Do violence to no man, neither accuse any falsely,

02:31.080 --> 02:33.120
And be content with your wages.

02:34.380 --> 02:39.600
And as the people were in expectation, and all men mused in their hearts of John

02:39.600 --> 02:44.420
Whether he were the Christ or not, John answered, saying unto them all,

02:44.720 --> 02:48.940
I indeed baptize you with water, but one mightier than I cometh,

02:49.380 --> 02:53.020
The latchet of whose shoes I am not worthy to unloose.

02:53.400 --> 02:57.260
He shall baptize you with the Holy Ghost and with fire,

02:58.040 --> 03:01.960
Whose fan is in his hand, and he will throughly purge his floor,

03:01.960 --> 03:06.000
And will gather the wheat into his garner, but the chaff he will burn

03:06.000 --> 03:07.840
With fire unquenchable.

03:08.460 --> 03:12.160
And many other things in his exhortation preached he unto the people.

03:13.520 --> 03:18.080
But Herod the Tetrarch, being reproved by him for Herodias,

03:18.140 --> 03:22.620
His brother Philip's wife, and for all the evils which Herod had done,

03:23.500 --> 03:27.040
Added yet this above all, that he shut up John in prison.

03:27.740 --> 03:32.020
Now when all the people were baptized, it came to pass that Jesus also,

03:32.160 --> 03:35.540
Being baptized and praying, the heaven was opened,

03:35.960 --> 03:40.900
And the Holy Ghost descended in a bodily shape like a dove upon him,

03:41.120 --> 03:43.560
And a voice came from heaven which said,

03:44.080 --> 03:48.320
Thou art my beloved Son, in thee I am well pleased.

03:49.680 --> 03:53.260
And Jesus himself began to be about thirty years of age,

03:53.260 --> 03:59.040
Being, as was supposed, the son of Joseph, which was the son of Heli,

03:59.400 --> 04:02.300
Which was the son of Methat, which was the son of Levi,

04:02.840 --> 04:06.280
Which was the son of Melchai, which was the son of Janna,

04:06.600 --> 04:10.560
Which was the son of Joseph, which was the son of Mountathias,

04:10.760 --> 04:13.660
Which was the son of Amos, which was the son of Naum,

04:14.120 --> 04:18.540
Which was the son of Ezli, which was the son of Negei,

04:18.540 --> 04:22.420
Which was the son of Meath, which was the son of Mountithias,

04:22.420 --> 04:28.140
which was the son of Simei which was the son of Joseph, which was the son of Judah

04:28.140 --> 04:33.840
which was the son of Joan which was the son of Risa which was the son of Zorah Babel

04:34.240 --> 04:38.320
which was the son of Silatheal which was the son of neirai

04:39.500 --> 04:45.080
which was the son of Melkai which was the son of Adai which was the son of Kosem

04:45.080 --> 04:49.340
which was the son of Elmodam which was the son of Er

04:49.920 --> 04:54.940
Which was the son of Josiah, which was the son of Eliezer, which was the son

04:54.940 --> 05:01.280
of Joram, which was the son of Mawthat, which was the son of Levi, which was the

05:01.280 --> 05:05.720
son of Simeon, which was the son of Judah, which was the son of Joseph, which

05:05.720 --> 05:11.960
was the son of Jonan, which was the son of Eliakim, which was the son of Malaeh,

05:12.300 --> 05:17.400
which was the son of Menun, which was the son of Mattatha, which was the son of

05:17.400 --> 05:23.380
Nathan which was the son of David, which was the son of Jesse which was the son of Obed

05:23.380 --> 05:29.500
which was the son of Boaz which was the son of Salmon which was the the son of Na Large

05:29.500 --> 05:36.800
which was the son of Amenadab which was the son of Aram which was the son of Esraam which

05:36.800 --> 05:43.080
was the son of Phares which was the son of Judah which was the Son of Jacob which was

05:43.080 --> 05:49.100
son of Isaac, which was the son of Abraham, which was the son of Thera, which

05:49.100 --> 05:54.940
was the son of Nakor, which was the son of Saruk, which was the son of Raegaw,

05:55.280 --> 06:00.500
which was the son of Phalech, which was the son of Heber, which was the son of

06:00.500 --> 06:07.120
Salah, which was the son of Kainin, which was the son of Arphaxad, which was the

06:07.120 --> 06:14.700
of Sem, which was the son of Noah, which was the son of Lesmik, which was the son of Methuselah,

06:14.880 --> 06:20.320
which was the son of Enoch, which was the son of Jared, which was the son of M container,

06:20.840 --> 06:26.740
which was the son of Kaim That is, which was the son of Einus, which was the son of Seth,

06:27.260 --> 06:31.640
which was the son of Adam, which was the son of God.

06:33.640 --> 06:40.780
4. And Jesus, being full of the Holy Ghost, returned from Jordan, and was led by the Spirit

06:40.780 --> 06:47.080
into the wilderness, being forty days tempted of the devil. And in those days he did eat

06:47.080 --> 06:53.240
nothing, and when they were ended he afterward hungered. And the devil said unto him, If

06:53.240 --> 06:59.440
thou be the Son of God, command this stone, that it be made bread. And Jesus answered

06:59.440 --> 07:05.440
him, saying, It is written, that man shall not live by bread alone, but by every word

07:05.440 --> 07:13.060
of God. And the devil, taking him up into an high mountain, showed unto him all the

07:13.060 --> 07:19.460
kingdoms of the world in a moment of time. And the devil said unto him, All this power

07:19.460 --> 07:25.920
will I give thee, and the glory of them, for that is delivered unto me, and to whomsoever

07:25.920 --> 07:34.440
I will I give it. If thou therefore wilt worship me, all shall be thine. And Jesus answered

07:34.440 --> 07:39.740
and said unto him, Get thee behind me, Satan, for it is written, Thou shalt worship the

07:39.740 --> 07:46.340
Lord thy God, and him only shalt thou serve. And he brought him to Jerusalem, and said

07:46.340 --> 07:52.060
him on a pinnacle of the temple, and said unto him, If thou be the Son of God, cast

07:52.060 --> 07:58.540
thyself down from hence. For it is written, He shall give his angels charge over thee

07:58.540 --> 08:04.680
to keep thee, and in their hands they shall bear thee up, lest at any time thou dash thy

08:04.680 --> 08:11.300
foot against a stone. And Jesus answering said unto him, It is said, Thou shalt not

08:11.300 --> 08:17.560
tempt the Lord thy God. And when the devil had ended all the temptation, he departed from

08:17.560 --> 08:25.800
him for a season. And Jesus returned in the power of the Spirit into Galilee. And there

08:25.800 --> 08:31.800
went out a fame of him through all the region round about, and he taught in their synagogues,

08:31.920 --> 08:38.860
being glorified of all. And he came to Nazareth where he had been brought up, and as his custom

08:38.860 --> 08:45.160
was, he went into the synagogue on the Sabbath day, and stood up for to read. And there was

08:45.160 --> 08:50.620
delivered unto him the book of the prophet Isaiah. And when he had opened the book, he

08:50.620 --> 08:56.480
found the place where it was written. The Spirit of the Lord is upon me, because he

08:56.480 --> 09:02.280
hath anointed me to preach the gospel to the poor. He hath sent me to heal the brokenhearted,

09:02.840 --> 09:08.320
to preach deliverance to the captives, and recovering of sight to the blind, to set at

09:08.320 --> 09:15.140
liberty them that are bruised, to preach the acceptable year of the Lord. And he closed

09:15.140 --> 09:21.120
the book, and he gave it again to the minister, and sat down. And the eyes of all them that

09:21.120 --> 09:28.240
were in the synagogue were fastened on him. And he began to say unto them, This day is

09:28.240 --> 09:34.660
this scripture fulfilled in your ears. And all bare him witness, and wondered at the

09:34.660 --> 09:41.440
gracious words which proceeded out of his mouth. And they said, Is not this Joseph's

09:41.440 --> 09:49.020
son? And he said unto them, Ye will surely say unto me this proverb, Physician, heal

09:49.020 --> 09:56.880
thyself. Whatsoever we have heard done in Capernaum, do also hear in thy country. And he said,

09:57.660 --> 10:05.740
Verily I say unto you, No prophet is accepted in his own country. But I tell you of a truth,

10:06.320 --> 10:11.500
Many widows were in Israel in the days of Elias, when the heaven was shut up three years

10:11.500 --> 10:18.920
and six months, when great famine was throughout all the land. But unto none of them was Elias

10:18.920 --> 10:26.020
sent save unto Serepta, a city of Sidon, unto a woman that was a widow. And many lepers

10:26.020 --> 10:31.800
were in Israel in the time of Elishaias the prophet. And none of them was cleansed, saving

10:31.800 --> 10:38.400
Naaman the Syrian. And all they in the synagogue when they heard these things were filled

10:38.400 --> 10:44.760
with wrath, and rose up and thrust him out of the city, and led him unto the brow of

10:44.760 --> 10:51.500
the hill whereon their city was built, that they might cast him down headlong. But he

10:51.500 --> 10:57.620
passing through the midst of them went his way, and came down to Capernaum a city of

10:57.620 --> 11:05.600
them on the Sabbath days. And they were astonished at his doctrine, for his word was with power.

11:06.340 --> 11:11.780
And in the synagogue there was a man which had a spirit of an unclean devil, and cried

11:11.780 --> 11:17.740
out with a loud voice, saying, Let us alone. What have we to do with thee, thou Jesus of

11:17.740 --> 11:24.280
Nazareth? Art thou come to destroy us? I know thee, who thou art, the Holy One of God.

11:25.130 --> 11:32.200
And Jesus rebuked him, saying, Hold thy peace, and come out of him. And when the devil had

11:32.200 --> 11:38.480
thrown him in the midst, he came out of him, and hurt him not. And they were all amazed

11:38.480 --> 11:44.800
and spake among themselves, saying, What a word is this? For with authority and power

11:44.800 --> 11:51.020
he commandeth the unclean spirits, and they come out. And the fame of him went out into

11:51.020 --> 11:57.180
every place of the country round about. And he arose out of the synagogue, and entered

11:57.180 --> 12:04.060
into Simon's house. And Simon's wife's mother was taken with a great fever, and they

12:04.060 --> 12:10.240
besought him for her. And he stood over her, and rebuked the fever, and it left her, and

12:10.240 --> 12:16.900
immediately she arose and ministered unto them. Now when the sun was setting, all they

12:16.900 --> 12:23.560
that had any sick with diverse diseases brought them unto him. And he laid his hands on every

12:23.560 --> 12:30.440
one of them, and healed them. And devils also came out of many, crying out, and saying,

12:30.920 --> 12:37.960
Thou art Christ, the Son of God. And he rebuking them, suffered them not to speak, for they

12:37.960 --> 12:43.720
knew that he was Christ. And when it was day, he departed, and went into a desert place.

12:44.080 --> 12:49.300
And the people sought him, and came unto him, and stayed him, that he should not depart

12:49.300 --> 12:56.880
from them. And he said unto them, I must preach the kingdom of God to other cities also, for

12:56.880 --> 13:02.760
therefore am I sent. And he preached in the synagogues of Galilee.

